Comment.val:
- If an unprocessed lump sum is present in the pay-out series, all other pay-out (regular and incidental) must be sent to Wealth Manager as an amount order.
Order amount will be calculated as follows:
1) First the portfolio value is determined. 2) Amount = (portfolio value - lump sum amount)*percentage.
- For lumpsum (BBD_TYPE =2): The order to Wealth Manager will always be amount order.
- Without lumpum in the pay-out serie: The order to Wealth Manager will always be percentage order.
